verbose_text: Urea, serum creatinine (Scr), uric acid (UA), total serum cholesterol (TCH), serum triglycerides (TG), and serum high- and low-density lipoprotein (HDL and LDL) cholesterol levels were obtained from the clinical examination of a fasting blood sample within 7 days of the CT examination in the Clinical Laboratory of the Renmin Hospital of Wuhan University.
